[3]
Date: 27 February 2008
Source: Australian Broadcasting Corporation Rural News [edited]
<http://www.abc.net.au/rural/news/content/200802/s2173929.htm>


Smut spreads across Queensland
------------------------------
Sugarcane smut continues to spread across Queensland, with the fungal
disease found yesterday [26 Feb 2008] on a property in the Innisfail area.
The latest find is the most northerly outbreak, and Joseph Morano from
Canegrowers says it has infected a popular cane variety. "The variety that
smut was found on is Q166, it's a very good variety for the dry areas of
the district," he says. "It's one of our major varieties and there's not
too much you can replace it with at this stage either, so that is a concern
to people."

